consent_prescreen:
It is very helpful for us if we can link your responses to this questionnaire to responses you provided in the prescreen questions you have filled out.
If you are okay with us combining your prescreen data with your responses to this questionnaire please enter your UTORid below, thanks! 🙏
social_media_time: Approximately how much time (in minutes) do you spend using social media each day?
social_media_freq: Approximately how many times a day do you use social media?
weight:
Please enter your weight in pounds.
If you only know your weight in kilograms please multiply that number by 2.2 before entering.
height#1_1: Please enter your height in feet and inches. - Feet - Height
height#2_1: Please enter your height in feet and inches. - Inches - Height
gpa_current_44:
What was your GPA for your most recent semester (sessional GPA)?
 

See the conversion table below if necessary: - GPA
performance_compare_1:
When you think about the other people in your program, where do you think you are in comparison? 
 

Answer this in percentile terms - which you can think of as how many people are above and below you.

 

For example, if are at the 90th percentile you can think of this as having:

 


	10 people above you
	YOU
	89 people below you

Think of what proportion of your class is above and below you and make a selection... - Percentile
overall_success_pre_1:
Intention/Goal Success



When you consider the intentions or goals that you have for yourself, to what degree do you feel like you are successful in actually accomplishing those goals?

 

Please consider both big and small intentions or goals.
Also keep in mind your goal might be either to do something or not to do something.



	100% success rate would mean that you are able to accomplish ALL of your goals/intentions.
	50% success rate would mean that you are able to accomplish about HALF of your goals/intentions. - Goal success rate (%)
ib_domains_goal_diet:
Domain Questions

 

Below we list a wide variety of categories where you may have goals.



We would like to know, for each category, whether or not you have actual goals for that particular category.
Remember that the goals do not have to be specific, even if you have a general or vague goal then indicate that you DO have a goal for that category. 



For example, one person may have a goal to cook their own dinner every night while you might not care at all whether you cook or eat out or order take out.


Also, goals can be either a desire to DO something as well as a desire to NOT DO something. - Diet

ib_domains_specific_diet:
Domain | Goal Specificity

 

Please indicate to what degree your goals are general or specific.

 

A specific sleep goal might be something like going to bed at 10:15pm every night and waking up at 6:30am. 

 

A general sleep goal might be much more vague, for example having in mind that you would like to get 8 hours of sleep when possible.

 



The response scale runs from 1-7, where 1 indicates that your goal is very general and 7 indicates that your goal is very specific. - Diet

ib_domains_locus_diet:
Domains | Gap Cause

 

How much do you feel that any gap that exists between your intentions and behavior is caused by internal vs. external factors?

 

In other words if the gap is due to your own capabilities, limitations, or actions, then it is internal.

 

If the gap is caused by outside forces that you cannot control (e.g. illness, weather, sexism or other systemic factors, etc.) then it is external. - Diet

debrief_form_1:
University of Toronto, Scarborough

Debriefing Form


Principle Investigator: Cendri Hutcherson, Ph.D., Assistant Professor of PsychologProject Name: Tracking the gap between goals and outcomes in daily behavior
Thank you for participating in our study! 
We designed this study to better understand how people might experience a gap between their intentions and behavior, both at a day to day level, and at a broader life level. We hope to develop a better measurement of this gap that is reliable across contexts and across individuals. 
Please understand that your participation in the research is voluntary and that you are free to withdraw your consent and data in the research at this time without any penalties. That is, you will receive full credit and payment for taking part in the study. Should you choose to withdraw from the study, all of the information that we obtained from your session will be destroyed.
Thank you for your time and effort in our study. If you have any questions about the research, you may feel free and contact Dr. Cendri Hutcherson at c.hutcherson@utoronto.ca or (416) 208-4826.
If you have any questions about your rights or treatment as a participant in this research project, please contact the University of Toronto’s Office of Research Ethics at ethics.review@utoronto.ca or (416) 946-3273.
We also ask that you do not discuss this study with anyone outside of our research team, so that potential future participants will not be biased to behave in a certain way before participating in the study.
Participant Consent By clicking below, you consent to give the principal investigator permission to use your data for this research project. - I consent for my data to be analyzed by the research team
